On July 1, 2019, President Trump signed the Taxpayer First Bill, which streamlines changes to the IRS. He also signed a bill to provide $4.6 billion in humanitarian assistance to the southern border, including funding for medical care, shelters, and increased housing for minors. President Trump thanked Mexico for its efforts in border security and stated that a bill for border security is necessary to solve the problem entirely. He also called for the elimination of incentives for smuggling children and women across the border. The President discussed the construction of the wall and criticized a Ninth Circuit judge's ruling that affected its construction. He urged Congress to provide humane solutions and eliminate catch-and-release policies. President Trump also addressed issues such as trade talks with China, the census, derogatory comments made by Border Patrol agents, and plans for a Fourth of July celebration in Washington, D.C.